SIMPLE: maravilla
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: maravilla
<hw>maravilla</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A wildflower
(<spn>Mirabilis multiflora</spn>) having vibrant deep pink tubular
evening-blooming flowers; found in sandy and desert areas from Southern
California to Southern Colorado and into Mexico.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> desert four o'clock, Colorado four o'clock,
<spn>Mirabilis multiflora</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A leafy wildflower (<spn>Mirabilis longiflora</spn>)
having fragrant slender white or pale pink trumpet-shaped flowers; found
in the Southwestern US and Northern Mexico.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> sweet four o'clock, <spn>Mirabilis
longiflora</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Marble</ent>⟦br⟧
